Maranda High School dormitory on fire [Isaiah Gwengi, Standard]  Bondo Deputy County Commissioner, Richard Karani has confirmed that Maranda High School, Siaya County is on fire again.  Speaking to The Standard on Sunday, December 5 morning, Karani said that the fire began at the Boaz Owino a few minutes ago adding that the police have just arrived at the school to establish more details.  "We have just been informed that the fire began this morning. We are on our way to look into it," Karan told The Standard.  On Thursday, all Form Four students were sent home indefinitely for allegedly refusing to write mock exams and threatening to burn the school.  All 400 Maranda School Form 4 students sent home indefinitely  Parents to know fate in Sh21 million school fire case  Teacher testifies in Lang’ata Boys’ dormitory fire case against 12 students  Kakamega High parents to know fate in Sh21m case next week Firefighting department in efforts to put out the fire [Collins Oduor, Standard]  Siaya County Director of Education Nelson Sifuna confirmed to The Standard that over 400 students were sent home on Thursday morning.  “The internal mock exams, which were scheduled for Monday, December 6, have since been postponed to a later date, which will be communicated,” he said.  Sifuna said the students had, on Tuesday night, threatened to torch learning or accommodation facilities within the school.  One of the teachers of Maranda High School, who spoke to The Standard on condition of anonymity, said the decision to send the learners home was arrived at on Thursday morning.  ...More to follow...   Report: Kenyan pupils assaulted their teachers  Watu 10 wapoteza maisha yao na wengine wajeruhiwa kutokana na moto Uganda  Youth on school fires: Students speak out on recent unfortunate events By Nicholas Mburu | 3 hours ago By Edwin Nyarangi | 6 hours ago By James Omoro | 1 day ago By Harold Odhiambo and Isaiah Gwengi | 1 day ago